The government has stopped education institutions from accessing loans to fund projects, citing abuse.  Education PS Belio Kipsang on Saturday said the facility has been abused by school heads. Kipsang said disciplinary action would be taken against managers who disregard this directive The move is part of reforms in the education sector, which aim at making learning more affordable and accessible to all Kenyans. Many institutions are struggling with huge debts after they failed to repaytheir  loans. “We have several applications from the institutions requesting the ministry’s clearance to borrow. We have said no and the directives is clear,” Kipsang said. He spoke at Our Lady of Victory Girls’ High School, Kapnyeberai, Nandi during the institutions prize-giving day. Kipsang said tough reforms will continue to be effected in the sector.  Click here for the latest political news